snippet.textDisplay:
The sad thing is all these peoples arguments are weak, terribly vocalised and have no factual basis. None of them seem capable of giving any real argument or facts about climate change. It would be cool if some people did actually do some research and come up with an opinion of their own or be able to actually quote some genuine stats. in 5 minutes and 30 seconds the only argument sated against him was that by 2075 the earth will be unlivable which is quite literally bullshit. No wonder nothing is changing, you have a bunch of people repeating what others have told them and coming up with nothing remotely intelligent as an argument to persuade people who are against climate action. Nor do they come up with any ways of fixing the problem. Ultimately carbon emissions are not the only major issue being faced and if you all actually did something for the environment maybe you would have a better scope of what the issues are. I'm sure many of you have two showers a day and water your lawn on the weekend. Look up your local land care group and see how you can get involved, take up the government solar re-bait, bike, bus, electric car, veggie oil car, ethanol car, methanol car, plant trees, pick up rubbish (And stop fucking littering, yes you, after the last protest i was at there was litter everywhere), don't buy products from companies that you deem unethical, stop using climate change as reason to diss and hate on people who are misinformed but learn some genuine techniques of helpful discussion to persuade people, stop buying and reading news from sources who support our corrupt government, reduce your consumption, Grow and hunt as much food as you can, stop buying useless fucking appliances, and clothes made by Aussie grown cotton, the sooner you realise that your decisions have a massive impact on the way a system is built the better. The numbers don't lie, we are all consuming at a rate of knots. The government cannot save the fucking environment, and they didn't destroy it. WE all did, and the sooner you take responsibility the sooner others will as well. As someone who is actually actively involved in land care i would say that many of the so called "environmentalists" have let us down more than anyone, sellout morons posing as "enviro-gurus" who get bought out by the government at the drop of a dime. Groups put together and payed for by tax payers with one job (to protect nature and its resources) who have failed us for years. I've seen them with my own eyes, people who are being payed to protect the environment, but quickly fall into the category of useless public servants which feel no need to achieve anything because they are instantly swept up in the slack culture of Australian government. Not to mention corrupt organisations like fisheries, pirsa the murray darling basin authority. Protesting for a good cause is great, but something is wrong when the organiser of the protest literally cant create a FAKE argument let alone muster a single piece of evidence to suggest climate change is man made and impacts bush fires in Australia. NO, Fire fighters saying "its global" warming IS NOT evidence to support global warming being a man made problem. And its sad that this has become the main point especially from an indigenous person who should know all too well that the stopping of indigenous burn off over a hundred years ago is a massive contributor to large scale bushfires now. As well as the fact that we are in a 20 year drought, which is likely caused by human made climate change, but also occurred pre-industrial humans. So no, you cannot just directly link the two without genuine evidence.
Personally i'm certain the recent extremity of bushfires is related to man made climate change, but i haven't heard many arguments from so called activists that should lead me to think this. If you don't think its your responsibility to do something then why should anyone else? Would it be good for the government to tax us more and give it to government employees to waste away in a snail paced bureaucracy, or would it be good for you to just save some money that you spend on shit that's bad for the environment and then in return spend it directly on something that's good for the environment whether it be time in hours, sacrifices of indulgences, or money in logical decisions that are more ethical and help the environment. I'd like them both, minus the "snail pace" and the quickest way we get there is by everyone leading by example AND FOR CHRIST SAKE LEARN A COUPLE FACTS AND STATISTICS THAT ACTUALLY RELATE TO YOUR ARGUMENT AND LEARN TO SAY THEM IN A WAY THAT ISN'T JUST HATING ON SOMEONE. Climate deniers are not stupider than you, they are just less informed. Inform them, don't create a battle against them because the real enemy is your own lack of responsibility and an inability to take responsibility for something which is all our problem to fix. And quite literally nothing good has ever come from chaotic yelling except maybe some great bands.
